        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring Systems",
          "Answering the Next Question Correctly",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "4217 Assist09 learners, 1079 Assist17, 574 Algebra05, 331 Statics",
          "Algebra & Engineering Statics",
          "Answers, Knowledge Concept Mapping",
          "[Sequences of student responses to questions]",
          "Prior KT models tend to overfit to patterns of responses instead of tracing stable underlying knowledge states; they suffer from information bias where inferred states change abruptly after single responses.",
          "Proposes Diagnostic Transformer (DTransformer) with Temporal and Cumulative Attention (TCA) and a contrastive learning training paradigm to achieve stable knowledge state tracing instead of mere pattern prediction.",
          "Uses Rasch embeddings for question–concept pairs; augments sequences with flip-response, item-drop, and swap-adjacent to enforce contrastive stability.",
          "DTransformer (full and w/o CL), DKT, DKT+, DKVMN, SAKT, AKT, CL4KT",
          "Holdout Method",
          "ASSIST09\n{MAE:  0.3097 - DTransformer, RMSE: 0.4062 - DTransformer w/o CL, Accuracy: 0.7579 - DTransformer w/o CL, AUC: 0.8056 - DTransformer w/o CL}\n\nASSIST17\n{MAE:  0.3831 - DTransformer w/o CL, RMSE: 0.4385 - AKT, Accuracy: 0.7071 - AKT, AUC: 0.7464 - AKT}\n\nALGEBRA05\n{MAE:  0.2302 - DTransformer w/o CL, RMSE: 0.3423 - DTransformer w/o CL, Accuracy: 0.8392 - DTransformer w/o CL, AUC: 0.7891 - CL4KT}\n\nSTATICS\n{MAE:  0.2612 - DTransformer, RMSE: 0.3632 - DTransformer w/o CL, Accuracy: 0.7948 - DTransformer w/o CL, AUC: 0.8341 - DTransformer w/o CL}",
          "Authors argue that stable knowledge tracing is more faithful to the learning process. Visualization shows reduced sensitivity to slips/guesses.",
          "Validation limited to 4 datasets. Computational cost is higher. Stability evaluated indirectly via prediction decay rather than ground-truth knowledge."
        ]
      ],
