    {
      "id": "0317c828-c1a4-478a-992e-3bf4af7b786b",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Knowledge Tracing is intended to provide a representation of a student’s knowledge state: what knowledge does the learn possess. However, recent applications o KT modelling focus on understanding if next question will be answered correctly, which may result in the model’s only ktracing learning activities undertaken and not knowledge states.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "0317c828-c1a4-478a-992e-3bf4af7b786b",
        "parent": {
